1. @Target
    -> The scope of where it can be applied on.
2. @Retention
    -> When this has to be executed
    -> SOURCE - visible by neither the compiler nor the runtime
    -> CLASS - visible by the compiler (Default)
    -> RUNTIME - visible by the compiler and the runtime
3. @Inherited
    -> We can use the @Inherited annotation to make our annotation propagate from an annotated class to its subclasses.
4. @Documented
    -> By default, Java doesn’t document the usage of annotations in Javadocs.
    -> But, we can use the @Documented annotation to change Java’s default behavior.
5. @Repeatable
    -> we can make an annotation repeatable
